---
import MainLayout from '../../layouts/main.astro';
import BlogStructuredData from '../../components/BlogStructuredData.astro';

const title = "Free on Mobile: Why Deep Rock Galactic: Survivor Is One of 2025's Best Indie Imports";
const description = "Deep Rock Galactic: Survivor brings console mining action to mobile in 2025. Discover why this free-to-try indie auto-shooter is one of the year's most addictive mobile games.";
const publishDate = "2025-11-14";
const author = "smartly.sale Gaming Team";
const category = "Mobile Gaming";
const image = "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1556438064-2d7646166914?w=1200&h=630&fit=crop";
---

<MainLayout 
  title={title}
  description={description}
  ogImage={image}
>
  <BlogStructuredData 
    slug="deep-rock-galactic-survivor-mobile-2025"
    title={title}
    description={description}
    publishDate={publishDate}
    author={author}
    category={category}
    image={image}
  />

  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <!-- Hero Image -->
    <div class="mb-8">
      <img 
        src={image}
        alt="Deep Rock Galactic: Survivor mobile gaming"
        class="w-full h-[400px] object-cover rounded-lg shadow-lg"
      />
    </div>

    <!-- Header -->
    <header class="mb-8">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-4 text-foreground">
        {title}
      </h1>
      <div class="flex items-center text-muted-foreground text-sm mb-6">
        <time datetime={publishDate}>{new Date(publishDate).toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' })}</time>
        <span class="mx-2">•</span>
        <span>{category}</span>
      </div>
    </header>

    <!-- Article Content -->
    <div class="article-content">
      <p class="text-xl text-muted-foreground mb-8">
        The console hit Deep Rock Galactic: Survivor has officially landed on mobile devices in 2025, and it's taking the indie gaming community by storm. This free-to-try auto-shooter combines the beloved Deep Rock universe with addictive survivor-style gameplay perfectly optimized for touchscreens. Here's everything you need to know about this year's most exciting indie mobile import.
      </p>

      <h2>What Is Deep Rock Galactic: Survivor?</h2>
      <p>
        Deep Rock Galactic: Survivor is a reverse bullet-hell auto-shooter that puts you in the boots of a dwarf miner battling endless waves of alien bugs on hostile planets. Originally released on PC and console, the game has been meticulously ported to mobile with full touchscreen optimization.
      </p>

      <h3>Core Gameplay Mechanics</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Auto-Shooting Action:</strong> Your dwarf automatically fires at nearby enemies, letting you focus on positioning and dodging</li>
        <li><strong>Survivor-Style Progression:</strong> Each run lasts 15-30 minutes with permanent upgrades between attempts</li>
        <li><strong>Deep Rock Universe:</strong> Familiar characters, enemies, and weapons from the beloved franchise</li>
        <li><strong>Mining & Mayhem:</strong> Collect minerals while fighting off swarms of hostile creatures</li>
        <li><strong>Build Variety:</strong> Unlock weapons, perks, and abilities to create unique playstyles</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Why Mobile Gamers Are Going Crazy for It</h2>
      <p>
        Deep Rock Galactic: Survivor has hit a sweet spot that few mobile games achieve: console-quality gameplay that actually works better on mobile. Here's what makes it special:
      </p>

      <h3>Perfect Mobile Controls</h3>
      <p>
        Unlike many mobile ports that feel clunky, DRG: Survivor was designed with touchscreens in mind:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Simple one-finger movement controls</li>
        <li>No need for complex button combinations</li>
        <li>Auto-aim makes combat smooth and satisfying</li>
        <li>Responsive touch input with zero lag</li>
        <li>Landscape and portrait mode support</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Quick Gaming Sessions</h3>
      <p>
        Perfect for the mobile lifestyle:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Runs complete in 15-30 minutes</li>
        <li>Pick up and play instantly</li>
        <li>No forced tutorials or time-gating</li>
        <li>Offline play supported</li>
        <li>Battery-optimized graphics</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Free-to-Try Model Done Right</h3>
      <p>
        The monetization is fair and player-friendly:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Full game playable for free</li>
        <li>Optional premium version removes ads</li>
        <li>No pay-to-win mechanics</li>
        <li>All content unlockable through gameplay</li>
        <li>One-time purchase for full experience</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Game Modes and Content</h2>
      <p>
        DRG: Survivor packs surprising depth into its mobile package:
      </p>

      <h3>Standard Runs</h3>
      <p>
        The core experience where you'll spend most of your time:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Choose from multiple dwarf classes</li>
        <li>Select starting weapons and perks</li>
        <li>Survive increasingly difficult waves</li>
        <li>Collect minerals and power-ups</li>
        <li>Unlock new upgrades for future runs</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Challenge Modes</h3>
      <p>
        Special modes that test your skills:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Endless Mode:</strong> See how long you can survive</li>
        <li><strong>Speed Runs:</strong> Complete objectives in record time</li>
        <li><strong>Boss Rush:</strong> Face elite enemies back-to-back</li>
        <li><strong>Hardcore Mode:</strong> Permadeath with special rewards</li>
        <li><strong>Daily Challenges:</strong> New objectives every 24 hours</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Progression System</h3>
      <p>
        Permanent upgrades keep you coming back:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Unlock new dwarf classes with unique abilities</li>
        <li>Discover powerful weapons and equipment</li>
        <li>Purchase permanent stat boosts</li>
        <li>Complete achievements for bonus rewards</li>
        <li>Level up your account for new features</li>
      </ul>

