      <h2>Tips for New Players</h2>
      <p>
        Master Deep Rock Galactic: Survivor with these essential strategies:
      </p>

      <h3>Early Game Strategy</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Focus on Movement:</strong> Positioning is more important than damage early on</li>
        <li><strong>Prioritize Survivability:</strong> Health and shield upgrades before damage</li>
        <li><strong>Learn Enemy Patterns:</strong> Each bug type has predictable behaviors</li>
        <li><strong>Manage Your Space:</strong> Don't get cornered by swarms</li>
        <li><strong>Collect Everything:</strong> Minerals power your progression</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Build Optimization</h3>
      <p>
        Create powerful synergies:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Explosive Builds:</strong> Area damage for handling swarms</li>
        <li><strong>Single-Target Builds:</strong> High damage for bosses</li>
        <li><strong>Tank Builds:</strong> Maximum survivability for long runs</li>
        <li><strong>Speed Builds:</strong> High mobility for dodging</li>
        <li><strong>Hybrid Builds:</strong> Balanced stats for versatility</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Resource Management</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Save premium currency for permanent upgrades</li>
        <li>Don't waste resources on temporary boosts</li>
        <li>Complete daily missions for free rewards</li>
        <li>Watch optional ads for bonus minerals</li>
        <li>Prioritize unlocking new classes first</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Performance and Requirements</h2>
      <p>
        Deep Rock Galactic: Survivor runs smoothly on most modern devices:
      </p>

      <h3>Minimum Requirements</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Android:</strong> Android 8.0 or higher</li>
        <li><strong>iOS:</strong> iOS 13.0 or later</li>
        <li><strong>RAM:</strong> 3GB minimum (4GB recommended)</li>
        <li><strong>Storage:</strong> 800MB free space</li>
        <li><strong>Processor:</strong> Mid-range chipset from 2019+</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Graphics Settings</h3>
      <p>
        Adjust performance based on your device:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Low:</strong> Smooth 60fps on budget phones</li>
        <li><strong>Medium:</strong> Balanced quality and performance</li>
        <li><strong>High:</strong> Maximum visual fidelity</li>
        <li><strong>Ultra:</strong> Flagship devices only</li>
        <li>Frame rate lock options (30/60/120fps)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Comparing to Other Mobile Auto-Shooters</h2>
      <p>
        How does DRG: Survivor stack up against the competition?
      </p>

      <h3>vs. Vampire Survivors Mobile</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>DRG Advantage:</strong> More polished visuals and UI</li>
        <li><strong>DRG Advantage:</strong> Deeper progression system</li>
        <li><strong>VS Advantage:</strong> More character variety</li>
        <li><strong>VS Advantage:</strong> Lower price point</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>vs. Brotato Mobile</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>DRG Advantage:</strong> Superior production values</li>
        <li><strong>DRG Advantage:</strong> Better touchscreen controls</li>
        <li><strong>Brotato Advantage:</strong> More build variety</li>
        <li><strong>Brotato Advantage:</strong> Faster run times</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>vs. Magic Survival</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>DRG Advantage:</strong> More engaging theme</li>
        <li><strong>DRG Advantage:</strong> Better progression feedback</li>
        <li><strong>Magic Advantage:</strong> Completely free</li>
        <li><strong>Magic Advantage:</strong> Runs on older devices</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Community and Updates</h2>
      <p>
        The DRG: Survivor mobile community is thriving:
      </p>

      <h3>Active Development</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Regular content updates every 4-6 weeks</li>
        <li>New dwarf classes added quarterly</li>
        <li>Balance patches based on player feedback</li>
        <li>Bug fixes within 48-72 hours</li>
        <li>Community event weeks monthly</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Where to Connect</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Official Discord:</strong> Strategy discussions and dev updates</li>
        <li><strong>Reddit Community:</strong> Build guides and achievement help</li>
        <li><strong>YouTube:</strong> Gameplay videos and tutorials</li>
        <li><strong>Facebook Groups:</strong> Philippine gaming communities</li>
        <li><strong>Twitter/X:</strong> News and patch notes</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Monetization: What You Should Buy</h2>
