        <p class="text-sm">Pro tip: Wait for Shopee sales to grab Google Play or Apple App Store gift cards at a discount, then use them to purchase the premium version!</p>
      </div>

      <h2>Should You Download It?</h2>
      <p>
        Deep Rock Galactic: Survivor is a must-try for:
      </p>

      <h3>Perfect For You If...</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>You love survivor-style auto-shooters</li>
        <li>You want console-quality mobile games</li>
        <li>You enjoy short, repeatable gaming sessions</li>
        <li>You prefer skill-based progression over pay-to-win</li>
        <li>You're a fan of the Deep Rock Galactic universe</li>
        <li>You like games with active development</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Skip It If...</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>You prefer PvP competitive games</li>
        <li>You want story-driven experiences</li>
        <li>You dislike repetitive gameplay loops</li>
        <li>Your device doesn't meet requirements</li>
        <li>You're tired of the auto-shooter genre</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>The Verdict</h2>
      <p>
        Deep Rock Galactic: Survivor is one of the best indie game imports to hit mobile in 2025. The developers have nailed the delicate balance of preserving what made the original great while optimizing everything for touchscreen play. The free-to-try model is generous, the premium price is reasonable, and the gameplay is genuinely addictive.
      </p>
      <p>
        Whether you're a longtime Deep Rock Galactic fan or completely new to the franchise, this mobile version offers dozens of hours of engaging gameplay that respects your time and wallet. The polish, performance, and player-friendly monetization make it an easy recommendation for anyone who enjoys action-packed mobile gaming.
      </p>
      <p>
        Download it today, grab your pickaxe, and discover why gamers are calling this one of 2025's most addictive mobile experiences. Rock and stone, miner!
      </p>

      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <h3>Is Deep Rock Galactic: Survivor really free?</h3>
      <p>
        Yes, the full game is free to download and play. The free version includes optional ads and slightly slower progression. A one-time PHP 399 premium purchase removes ads and doubles mineral gains.
      </p>

      <h3>Do I need to play the original Deep Rock Galactic to understand this?</h3>
      <p>
        No, DRG: Survivor is completely standalone. Familiarity with the universe adds flavor, but the game explains everything you need to know.
      </p>

      <h3>Is it online or offline?</h3>
      <p>
        The game works both online and offline. Some features like daily challenges and leaderboards require internet, but core gameplay is fully offline.
      </p>

      <h3>How long does a typical run last?</h3>
      <p>
        Most runs last 15-30 minutes depending on your skill and build. Perfect for commutes or coffee breaks.
      </p>

      <h3>Does it drain battery quickly?</h3>
      <p>
        The game is well-optimized. On medium settings, expect 3-4 hours of gameplay on a full charge on most modern smartphones.
      </p>

      <h3>Are there ads in the free version?</h3>
      <p>
        Yes, optional ads appear between runs and can be watched for bonus rewards. They're never forced or intrusive. The premium version removes all ads.
      </p>

      <h3>Will my progress transfer between devices?</h3>
      <p>
        Yes, progress syncs via Google Play Games (Android) or Game Center (iOS) when logged in.
      </p>

